► 2ND PASS




♦ Sampler — Tiled Diffusion —OR— Ultimate Upscale (group node)


 — <upscale_factor>
   → defines the upscale factor (1.0 = no upscale)

 — <denoise>
   → recommended range {0.05-0.25}


 — <tile_size> + <tile_overlap>
   → parameters for optimal tile size calculation



 — ♦ Tiled Diffusion Settings ♦

 — <Use Upscale Model?>
   — *true*  → uses selected upscaler model
   — *false* → uses regular "Upscale Image By" node with lanczos method

  — <tile_batch_size>
    amount of tiles processed at once
    → reduce if low on VRAM


 — ♦ Ultimate Upscale Settings ♦

  — <mask_blur>
    increasing can help in case of tile-seam issues (highly unlikely)
  
  — <tiled_decode>
    helps save VRAM during VAE decoding
    → only useful to turn on if running oom during this step

nodes.title: Note ↑
widgets_values:
► SAVE SETTINGS

• Here you can select which pass outputs you want to save
  → "Final Pass" saves the last completed pass

• By default all save nodes are set up for lossless webp files with the <filename> *nth_pass_%Hours%Minutes%Seconds* 

save location → "ComfyUI\output\SD35_ReAwakening"


• Central Control
  → just an additional all-in-one control for convenience

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► INPAINTING

• can be run after any Pass
• can be run repeatedly
• proceeds to saving


♦ Inpainting — AIO (group node)

—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Mask Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — <grow_mask>
   → expands the provided masks

 — <gaussian_blur>
   → blurs the mask for smoother integration

 
—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Inpainting Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — <feather>
   → functions as <feather> and <noise_mask_feather>

 — <inpaint_size>
   → temporary size the masked area is upscaled to during generation
     → to control level of detail
   → does nothing when the masked area is larger already

— <noise_mask>
   — *enabled* : 
     → context aware
     → smooth seamless result
     → <denoise> acts as denoise

   — *disabled* : 
     → ignores context
     → allows forcing out of context content
     → requires further measures to blend in properly (inpainting)
     → <denoise> acts as opacity


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Sampler Settings ♦ ♦ ♦
 — textbox at the bottom → conditioning

nodes.title: Note ↓
widgets_values:
► ADETAILER PASS

• can be run after any Pass
• proceeds to saving or inpainting 


♦ ADetailer — AIO (group node)


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Detector Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <bbox_detector>
   → detects bbox containing the part to be ADetailed

 — <sam_model>
   → segment-anything-model to crop the target part out of the bbox

 — <segm_detector>
   → detects the cropped out shape and masks correspondingly

 — <bbox_threshold>
   → probability of the detected part to match the query
   examples:
   — faces : detected very well → higher values work well ~0.7-0.8
   — hands : more difficult to distinguish → lower values ~0.4-0.5

 — <bbox_dilation>
   → expansion of the detected bboxes

 — <crop_factor>
   → multiple of the bbox area to be considered as context

 — <drop_size>
   → size in pixels below which a detection will be disregarded
   → to avoid over-detailing negligible background details

 
—• ♦ ♦ ♦ ADetailer Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — <guide_size>
   → size maximum for detections to be considered
   → allows skipping areas that are large/detailed enough already
   → when <force_inpaint> is enabled, guide_size will be disregarded

 — <inpaint_size>
   → temporary size the masked area is upscaled to during generation
     → to control level of detail
   → does nothing when the masked area is larger already

 — <feather>
   → functions as <feather> and <noise_mask_feather>

 — <noise_mask>
   —• *enabled* : 
      → context aware
      → smooth seamless result
      → <denoise> acts as denoise

   —• *disabled* : 
      → ignores context
      → allows forcing out of context content
      → requires further measures to blend in properly (inpainting)
      → <denoise> acts as opacity

 — <force_inpaint>
   → bypasses threshold and size criteria when enabled


—• ♦ ♦ ♦ Sampler Settings ♦ ♦ ♦

 — textbox at the bottom → conditioning

nodes.title: Note — Hello!
widgets_values:
—Hello and thanks for downloading this workflow!—

► Designed as a general purpose workflow with modular parts that can be toggled on/off, giving SD35 a flying start! 

Metadata saving is built in


I hope you enjoy it as much as I do!


► Features :

   • Installation and download guide for models and nodes
   • Full metadata support; recognized by CivitAI
   • Multiple passes with optional upscales
       → 1st Pass : Regular sampling with metadata processing
       → 2nd Pass : (opt.) Tiled Diffusion — or — UltimateSDUpscale
       → ADetailer  (opt. after 1st, 2nd or 3rd Pass)
       → Inpainting (opt. final pass)
